subSubSection.paragraph:
Thomas in 1893 noted only size differences from Margaret's Ranee Mouse (
H. margarettae
), and descriptive notes for that species will thus apply also to the Sundaic Ranee Mouse. Tail of holotype measures 183% of head-body length. Musser and Carleton reported that Philippine specimens have paler underside on head and body, and paler hindfeet than those from Borneo, with additionalslight differences in dental traits.
